            <thetext>If the DOM element to be used as the root node for an Inline application has its size set implicitly (e.g. if it has any child elements) as opposed to an explicit style declaration, the root node will continually grow after the application is started.

Steps to reproduce:
1) Create a new Inline skeleton application.
2) In the application&#39;s index.html, remove the &quot;height&quot; style declaration for #isle
3) Add some random text to &lt;div id=&quot;isle&quot;&gt;.
4) Build the application and open it in any browser.</thetext>
